race.comment: THURSAIN (8) returns from a 41-week spell for a third campaign. Made ground in each of her runs last prep but just missed the placings on every occasion. Two recent trials will have her up to the mark and ready to make a bright return. LORD VETTORI (1) is back from a six-month break. Closed the last campaign with three straight minor placings, the latest over 1300m at Dubbo where he led for home. Trialled in good style at Wyong on 10 November. Should be in the thick of things. JOANJETT (12) is a Written Tycoon filly from the Matthew Dunn stable on debut. Placed in a recent Deagon trial. Always regard highly the runners from this yard. CALL TO COURAGE (9) is back from a 23-week lay-off. Lightly raced filly who won a Gold Coast trial in good style almost a month ago. Betting will paint the picture. DAITANNA (6) has been kept fresh since a moderate return at Eagle Farm 39 days ago. Recent trial winner who might be about to find some form.
